<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05016l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05016l">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05016l"> 16(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">T</font> tries to kill Moses at an inn</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Balaam, however, did not reflect that as the Lord had changed his mind once he might change it twice; and the omission nearly cost him his life. He was unfortunately ignorant of what happened to Moses on a similar occasion. After the Lord had dispatched the Jewish prophet to Egypt to rescue his people from bondage, <mark>he met him at an inn</mark>, where they seem to have both put up for the night, and <mark>sought to kill him</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Balaam&apos;s Ass] 130</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
